# Next.js 15 App Router Cursor Rules

## Architecture
- Use App Router (`app/` directory), not Pages Router
- Default to Server Components — add `'use client'` only when necessary
- Use route groups `(group)` for layout organization without URL impact
- Co-locate page-specific components in the route directory

## File Conventions
- `page.tsx` — Route UI (required for route to be accessible)
- `layout.tsx` — Shared UI wrapping children (persists across navigations)
- `loading.tsx` — Loading UI with automatic Suspense boundary
- `error.tsx` — Error UI with automatic Error Boundary
- `not-found.tsx` — 404 UI
- `route.ts` — API Route handler (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)

## Data Fetching
- Fetch data in Server Components using `async/await` directly
- Use `fetch()` with Next.js caching: `{ cache: 'force-cache' }` (default), `{ cache: 'no-store' }`, or `{ next: { revalidate: 3600 } }`
- DON'T: Use `useEffect` for data fetching in Server Components
- DON'T: Create API routes just to fetch data in Server Components
- DO: Use Server Actions for mutations (`'use server'`)

## Server Actions
- Define in separate files with `'use server'` at the top
- Use `useActionState` for form state management
- Validate inputs with Zod before processing
- Always `revalidatePath()` or `revalidateTag()` after mutations
- Return structured responses: `{ success: boolean, data?, error? }`

## Rendering Strategies
- Static (default): Pages pre-rendered at build time
- Dynamic: Use `cookies()`, `headers()`, or `searchParams` to opt into dynamic rendering
- Streaming: Use `loading.tsx` or `<Suspense>` for progressive rendering
- ISR: Use `revalidate` option for time-based revalidation

## Performance
- Use `next/image` for all images (automatic optimization)
- Use `next/link` for client-side navigation
- Use `next/font` for font optimization (no layout shift)
- Implement parallel routes for independent loading
- Use `generateStaticParams` for static generation of dynamic routes

## Metadata & SEO
- Export `metadata` object or `generateMetadata` function from pages/layouts
- Include `title`, `description`, `openGraph`, `twitter` metadata
- Use `sitemap.ts` and `robots.ts` for SEO

## Middleware
- Use `middleware.ts` at project root for auth, redirects, i18n
- Keep middleware lightweight — it runs on every request
- Use `matcher` config to limit which routes trigger middleware

## Environment Variables
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` — Exposed to browser (public)
- Without prefix — Server-only (secrets)
- DON'T: Expose API keys with `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix
